Gauteng education spokesperson Steve Mabona says the motive for the murder of a deputy principal is still unknown. Police are investigating. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police are investigating the murder of the Phomolong Secondary School deputy principal who was shot dead on Friday afternoon. The 50-year-old sustained five gunshot wounds outside the Tembisa school. READ: Deputy principal shot and killed Gauteng education spokesperson Steve Mabona says the motive is still unknown. "The police are investigating circumstances surrounding this matter," he said.